+{"id":"bd-3jjc.11","title":"E2E: RepoConvergence full lifecycle integration test","description":"Create a comprehensive integration test that exercises the full RepoConvergence lifecycle with structured JSON logging.

## IMPORTANT: Binary crate constraint
rchd is a binary crate (no lib.rs). Integration tests in rchd/tests/ cannot import internal modules. This test MUST be an inline #[cfg(test)] test in rchd/src/repo_convergence.rs alongside existing unit tests. Use a separate submodule: #[cfg(test)] mod integration_tests { ... }

## Scenario flow
1. Create RepoConvergenceService with real EventBus
2. Register 3 workers (w1, w2, w3) via update_required_repos
3. Set worker states: w1 fully synced (Ready), w2 missing repos (Drifting), w3 missing repos (Drifting)
4. Verify initial drift states via get_drift_state
5. Mark drifting workers w2, w3 as converging via mark_converging
6. Record convergence attempts: w2 succeeds (→ Ready), w3 fails with budget remaining (→ Drifting)
7. Record second attempt for w3: succeeds (→ Ready)
8. Verify final states: all three workers Ready
