 {"id":"bd-vvmd.2.9","title":"Add command-classification regression suite to protect non-compilation UX","description":"Add a dedicated regression suite to ensure new reliability logic does not degrade command classification behavior or accidentally intercept commands that must stay local. Focus on preserving user expectations for pass-through behavior while still capturing intended compilation offload cases.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Unit tests cover positive/negative classification for cargo/gcc/clang/make/ninja/bun patterns, including watch/piped/redirected/backgrounded exclusions.\n- Regression tests explicitly assert local pass-through for non-compilation and package-management commands (including bun install/add/remove/link, bun run/build/dev/repl, bunx).\n- Hook-mode integration tests verify fail-open behavior when classifier/preflight timing budgets are exceeded or preconditions are ambiguous.\n- E2E scenarios confirm no unintended remote interception side effects on representative real workflows.\n- Structured logs include classifier rationale, confidence, decision path, and fallback reason codes for every scenario.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-16T16:55:04.705571391Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-16T16:58:17.143089002Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["classification","e2e","fail-open","rch-rel-2026q1","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-vvmd.2.9","depends_on_id":"bd-vvmd.2.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-16T16:58:01.129835548Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-vvmd.2.9","depends_on_id":"bd-vvmd.3.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-16T16:58:01.329762751Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-vvmd.2.9","depends_on_id":"bd-vvmd.7.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-16T16:58:01.737484699Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-vvmd.2.9","depends_on_id":"bd-vvmd.7.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-16T16:58:01.533601438Z","cr